<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,909,1548]" pageId="5" pageNumber="540">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,354,1053,1079]" pageId="5" pageNumber="540">Comparison.</emphasis>
Material compared to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bate" authorityYear="1972" box="[610,806,1053,1079]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Pattersoncypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="5" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micropapillosa">
<emphasis box="[610,806,1053,1079]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="540">P. micropapillosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nº. DGEO-CTG-UFPE-1164) described and deposited by 
<bibRefCitation author="Tome, M. E. T. R. &amp; Lima Filho, M. F. &amp; Neumann, V. H. M. L." box="[186,394,1089,1116]" pageId="5" pageNumber="540" pagination="153 - 176" refId="ref17084" refString="Tome, M. E. T. R., Lima Filho, M. F. &amp; Neumann, V. H. M. L. (2014) Taxonomic studies of non-marine ostracods in the Lower Cretaceous (Aptian-lower Albian) of post-rift sequence from Jatoba and Araripe basins (Northeast Brazil): Stratigraphic implications. Cretaceous Research, 48, 153 - 176. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. cretres. 2013.12.007" type="journal article" year="2014">
Tome 
<emphasis box="[256,312,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="540">et al.</emphasis>
(2014)
</bibRefCitation>
in the 
<emphasis box="[471,1024,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="540">Ivan de Medeiros Tinoco Microfossils Collection.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,909,1548]" pageId="5" pageNumber="540">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,592,1125,1151]" pageId="5" pageNumber="540">Occurrence and associated fauna</emphasis>
. It was recorded in the Santo Antônio section, at the following depths (from base to top): 1.8; 2.65; 3.1; 4.25; 5.25; 4.25; 5.35 and 
<quantity box="[764,846,1161,1188]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.55" pageId="5" pageNumber="540" unit="m" value="5.55">5.55 m</quantity>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bate" authorityYear="1972" box="[858,1055,1161,1187]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Pattersoncypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="5" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micropapillosa">
<emphasis box="[858,1055,1161,1187]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="540">P. micropapillosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not associated with the species 
<emphasis box="[151,266,1197,1223]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="540">Alicenulla</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[273,441,1197,1223]" class="Ostracoda" family="Darwinulidae" genus="Alicenula" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="5" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leguminella">
cf. 
<emphasis box="[309,441,1197,1223]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="540">leguminella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Poag" authorityYear="1962" box="[455,591,1198,1223]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cuneocytheridae" genus="Dicrorygma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL,GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="5" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[455,591,1198,1223]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="540">Dicrorygma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Christensen" authorityYear="1965" box="[607,745,1197,1223]" class="Ostracoda" genus="Orthorygma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="5" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[607,745,1197,1223]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="540">Orthorygma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
?) 
<emphasis box="[775,884,1197,1223]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="540">dimorpha</emphasis>
and the species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephenson" authorityYear="1938" box="[1211,1413,1197,1223]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cytherideidae" genus="Perissocytheridea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="5" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1211,1413,1197,1223]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="540">Perissocytheridea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,909,1548]" pageId="5" pageNumber="540">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,358,1233,1259]" pageId="5" pageNumber="540">Observations</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bate" authorityYear="1972" box="[372,569,1233,1259]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Pattersoncypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="5" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micropapillosa">
<emphasis box="[372,569,1233,1259]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="540">P. micropapillosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not found in the same abundance as the other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bate" authorityYear="1972" box="[1259,1436,1234,1259]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Pattersoncypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="5" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1259,1436,1234,1259]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="540">Pattersoncypris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
so it is noteworthy because this genus was described for the first time in this basin. Further studies are required to assess whether this species is a synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Krommelbein &amp; Weber" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[644,786,1305,1331]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Pattersoncypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="5" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salitrensis">
<emphasis box="[644,786,1305,1331]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="540">P. salitrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<emphasis box="[823,958,1305,1331]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="540">
<taxonomicName box="[823,954,1305,1331]" class="Ostracoda" family="Alloiocyprideidae" genus="Hourcqia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="5" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angulata">P. angulata</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,909,1548]" pageId="5" pageNumber="540">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,511,1341,1367]" pageId="5" pageNumber="540">Stratigraphic distribution</emphasis>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[528,599,1341,1367]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="540">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, Araripe Basin, Santana Group, Romualdo Formation (Silva Telles Jr. &amp; Viana 1990; 
<bibRefCitation author="Poropat, S. F. &amp; Colin, J. P." box="[295,561,1377,1404]" pageId="5" pageNumber="540" pagination="699 - 719" refId="ref16238" refString="Poropat, S. F. &amp; Colin, J. P. (2012 b) Reassessment of the Early Cretaceous non-marine ostracod genera Hourcqia Krommelbein, 1965 and Pattersoncypris Bate, 1972 with the description of a new genus, Kroemmelbeincypris. Journal of Paleontology, 86, 699 - 719. https: // doi. org / 10.1666 / 11 - 140 R. 1" type="journal article" year="2012">Poropat &amp; Colin 2012b</bibRefCitation>
), interval dated as Aptian (
<bibRefCitation author="Regali, M. S. P." box="[862,1003,1377,1403]" pageId="5" pageNumber="540" pagination="163 - 171" refId="ref16461" refString="Regali, M. S. P. (1990) Biocronoestratigrafia e paleoambiente do Eocretaceo das bacias do Araripe (CE) e Rio do Peixe (PB), NE, Brasil. Simposio sobre a Bacia do Araripe e Bacias Interiores do Nordeste, 1, 163 - 171." type="journal article" year="1990">Regali 1990</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Coimbra, J. C. &amp; Arai, M. &amp; Carreno, A. L." box="[1015,1245,1377,1403]" pageId="5" pageNumber="540" pagination="687 - 698" refId="ref13416" refString="Coimbra, J. C., Arai, M. &amp; Carreno, A. L. (2002) Biostratigraphy of Lower Cretaceous microfossils from the Araripe Basin, northeastern Brazil. Geobios, 35, 687 - 698. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / S 0016 - 6995 (02) 00082 - 7" type="journal article" year="2002">
Coimbra 
<emphasis box="[1120,1177,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="540">et al.</emphasis>
2002
</bibRefCitation>
). Potiguar Basin, Alagamar Formation, Aptian (
<bibRefCitation author="Do Carmo, D. A. &amp; Whatley, R. &amp; Queiroz Neto, J. V. Q. &amp; Coimbra, J. C." box="[485,730,1413,1439]" pageId="5" pageNumber="540" pagination="790 - 799" refId="ref13890" refString="Do Carmo, D. A., Whatley, R., Queiroz Neto, J. V. Q. &amp; Coimbra, J. C. (2008) On the validity of two Lower Cretaceous non-marine ostracode genera: biostratigraphic and paleogeographic implications. Journal of Paleontology, 82, 790 - 799. https: // doi. org / 10.1666 / 07 - 008.1" type="journal article" year="2008">
Do Carmo 
<emphasis box="[609,664,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="540">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
). Cedro Basin, Crato Formation, interval dated as Aptian (Tomé 2007; 
<bibRefCitation author="Tome, M. E. T. R. &amp; Lima Filho, M. F." box="[224,529,1449,1475]" pageId="5" pageNumber="540" pagination="56 - 70" refId="ref17032" refString="Tome, M. E. T. R. &amp; Lima Filho, M. F. (2010) Ostracodes da Bacia de Cedro, Andar Alagoas, Estado de Pernambuco, NE, Brasil: Implicacoes paleoambientais e bioestratigraficas. Estudos Geologicos, 21, 56 - 70." type="journal article" year="2010">Tomé &amp; Lima Filho 2010</bibRefCitation>
). Jatobá Basin, Serra Negra, in strata correlated to the Crato Formation, upper Aptian (
<bibRefCitation author="Tome, M. E. T. R. &amp; Lima Filho, M. F. &amp; Neumann, V. H. M. L." box="[243,442,1485,1511]" pageId="5" pageNumber="540" pagination="153 - 176" refId="ref17084" refString="Tome, M. E. T. R., Lima Filho, M. F. &amp; Neumann, V. H. M. L. (2014) Taxonomic studies of non-marine ostracods in the Lower Cretaceous (Aptian-lower Albian) of post-rift sequence from Jatoba and Araripe basins (Northeast Brazil): Stratigraphic implications. Cretaceous Research, 48, 153 - 176. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. cretres. 2013.12.007" type="journal article" year="2014">
Tomé 
<emphasis box="[316,373,1485,1511]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="540">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
). In the present manuscript, it was observed in the Araripe Basin, Romualdo Formation, upper Aptian.
</paragraph>
